seaweed coffee, also colloquially called seaweed brew or plankton coffee.
bitter, salty, oily, and teal as the hair of a miku.

we decided hundreds of years ago to stop the travel from our deep marshes up to the arid regions where the regular beans grow. the effort was never worth the yield, and no one wanted to stay up there. we need water around our feet.

when we realized that the traders who were willing to do this journey for us could not meet our demands, or if they could we were unable to pay them, we set out to find some substitute in our local ecosystem.

