we tried many things. roots, vines, whatever beans would survive our climate. we tried to cultivate a coffee plant that could be grown closer to us. but our research was fruitless, and after a few generations, the endeavour was seen as an old and faded dream.

until, one day, a SEA_DEER beckoned us over to a shunned island in the marshlands, were everybody knew nothing good would thrive, and showed us the seaweed, just below the surface.

beautiful! we were in awe. this worthless island, filled with nothing but trouble, yet just below the waterline... the key to drinking coffee once again!